product_name: DermalogicaClear Start Breakout Clearing Foaming Wash
summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeVeganSustainable PackagingGive BackHSA/FSA eligibleDermalogica Clear Start Breakout Clearing Foaming Wash Cleanser clears away dead skin cells, dirt and excess oils that clog pores and cause breakouts.
details: DetailsBenefitsDives deep into pores, clearing dead skin cells and trapped oils to help wipe out existing and future breakoutsRecommend for those who struggle with "back-ne" - acne on the backGreat for those with large pores, oily skin and acne breakoutsKey IngredientsSalicylic Acid: clears pores, dead skin cells, and trapped oils to stop existing and prevent future breakoutsMeadowsweet Extract: an anti-inflammatory agent that protects against the production and secretion of excess sebumTea Tree, Lavender, Camellia and Balm Mint: help eliminate bacteria and calm irritated skinOrange Peel Extract: revives, energizes, and refreshes skinItem 2264975How To UseMorning and night, work a pea-sized amount into a lather in wet hands. Apply to dampened face and neck, massaging in circular motions while concentrating on areas of congestion and oiliness. Avoid eye area. Rinse thoroughly with warm water.Precautions: For external use only. Avoid contact with eyes. If contact occurs, flush thoroughly with water.IngredientsActive: Salicylic Acid 0.50%. Inactive: Water/Aqua/Eau, Cocamidopropyl Betaine, Sodium Lauroyl Methyl Isethionate, Acrylates/Beheneth-25 Methacrylate Copolymer, Polysorbate-20, Melaleuca Alternifolia (Tea Tree) Leaf Oil, Citrus Aurantium Dulcis (Orange) Peel Oil, Lavandula Angustifolia (Lavender) Oil, Oleanolic Acid, Butylene Glycol, Enantia Chlorantha Bark Extract, Disodium Cocoamphodiacetate, Spiraea Ulmaria Extract, Camellia Sinensis Leaf Extract, Porpyra Umbilicalis Extract, Glycyrrhiza Glabra (Licorice) Rhizome/Root Extract, Sodium Hydroxide, Ethylhexylglycerin, Phenoxyethanol.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Trying it
reviews.comments: I've got some really stubborn blackheads and have tried so many different types of facial cleanser that didn't help. I'm hoping since this comes from Ulta Beauty that this one will do the job of getting rid of these stubborn blackheads and hopefully will keep rid of them. I like how easily it lathers and the smell of it is nice

reviews.headline: Does the job
reviews.comments:
I was desperate for a vitamin C serum that worked on my skin (sensitive and dry) and would help with signs of aging (40 year old). It has brightened my skin over time and helped even my skin tone. My skin does look healthier. However, this wasn't an overnight transformation. It took about 2-3 weeks for the change to be noticeable. 

It does feel a little sticky on the skin but it absorbs quickly on my dry skin. It doesnt have any smell and layers well with my peptide and moisturizer. 

The only negative is the price. For now, the results seem to be worth the price but  I do think there are some cheaper options out there.

reviews.headline: Wow
reviews.comments: Wow! Is all I can say! I've been on a quest for the perfect skincare solution to combat my very dry, dull skin, and let me tell you—this serum has truly transformed my complexion. It's amazing how something so lightweight can deliver such fantastic results! I incorporate it into my usual routine as the last step, and the difference is staggering. My skin now feels nourished, glowy, and incredibly healthy. Plus, there's no overpowering scent to distract from its effectiveness. Finding the perfect product for my skincare routine has always been a challenge, especially when it comes to addressing my dry, dull skin. I can honestly say that this serum has completely transformed the way my skin looks and feels. After incorporating it as the final step in my usual regimen, I've noticed a remarkable change! My skin now radiates a natural glow that I didn't think was possible. The best part? It has no overpowering scent, making it so easy to use daily without any irritation. I genuinely can't recommend it enough—grateful for this little gem that has made such a positive impact on my skin journey! Gifted by dermalogica

faceoff_positive.comments: I don't normally write reviews because I never feel the need to.. with that being said I am a 16 year old girl with moderate acne and my mom bought me the clear start sample kit and I noticed results within 3 days. It was awesome so we bought the bigger bottles and I am so happy with the way my face, chest and back have cleared up! I would recommend this to everyone!
faceoff_positive.headline: love it

faceoff_negative.comments: I really wanted to love this, and it felt great on my skin! No new acne and my skin felt soft and smooth. Unfortunately, however, I believe I'm allergic to one of the main ingredients: Cocamidopropyl Betaine. I did a lot (I mean a LOT) of research on all the products I was using and what ingredients were in them, and I had suspicions it was this cleanser that was causing the dermatitis around my nose and chin. The area became very tender and stung. Apparently the Cocamidopropyl Betaine ingredient often causes cases of dermatitis on people with sensitive skin. I wanted to try the calming cleanser or the adult clearing wash but they have gluten in it and I'm celiac so I can't try those. I love all my other dermalogica products, unfortunately this one just didn't work for me. I'll keep trying! Definitely try this cleanser but be on the lookout for signs of irritation.
faceoff_negative.headline: Wanted to love this!
